especially if they can't get out of the car right away. Imagine -- extreme
heat coming from the dash area (actually just the air bag, but who's going
to think of that right after an accident?) and also the &quot;smoke&quot; in the air
(which is actually a powder that keeps the airbag from sticking together
while it is folded up, so that it inflates properly). In this suit-happy
society, this amounts to &quot;emotionally damaged&quot; people who were traumatized
