I've been very surprised by the people in this thread claiming that
airbags have killed children and adults in &quot;5mph crashes&quot;. That is simply
false. Airbags are designed to inflate in crashes of 18mph or faster into
a rigid barrier. That kind of a crash could also be caused by two cars,
each 9mph, hitting directly head on. (Oops, not that thread again)
In that fast a crash, an unbelted person without an airbag will make a
large spiderweb in the windshield with their head. These are not parking
lot fender benders or minor accidents. I feel sorry for the 7-yr old who
died... perhaps he would have lived without an airbag, however his case is
an exception to the rule.
Airbags save lives.
Airbags are most effective when used with a properly belted seatbelt.
If you choose not to use either, you're making a mistake.

