"/> There's a matter that isn't being addressed here yet. In a nutshell,
the sensors are a type of P/I transducer. However they are activated, the
physical (pressure) change of a crash is converted
to an electrical signal. It takes approximately 15 milliseconds for
this signal to reach the activating mechanism. My point is, that
ultimately the airbag is activated by an electrical signal. If
someone doesn't know what they're doing and are 'messing
around' with your fuse panels/junction boxes under the dash or
the hood, they can accidentally short circuit/activate the
mechanism. Thus, with all the distributor-less vehicles, computer
controls and modules, etc., everywhere, there is a much greater
chance of accidental deployment. TJ

